{{Youmay|the moral concept|[[The Balance (starship)|''The Balance'']], the [[Starship/Legends|starship]]}}
{{Quote|Between every user and the Force, there is the Balance. Between every Force-user and her enemies, there is the Balance. We serve the Balance by doing to our enemies what they do to us. If we fail, the Force itself will fall&hellip;|Alema Rar|<ref name="Legacy of the Force: Inferno">''[[Legacy of the Force: Inferno]]''</ref>}}
'''The Balance''' was a sense of honor followed by [[Alema Rar]] after [[Gender/Legends|her]] near-[[Death/Legends|death]] experience on [[Tenupe]]. She used her twisted sense of morality to justify her [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side]] actions. The general idea was a form of self-centered karma. Rar felt that the pain she suffered should be suffered by those who caused it; hence, anything that caused pain to the Solos, who were responsible for her mutilation, was good in her opinion.

